03:21.636 --> 03:23.855
- You see, we ought
to nourish the reader,

03:23.899 --> 03:26.075
even if it's
only a little bit.

03:26.118 --> 03:29.861
Stir his brain,
move his heart.

03:29.905 --> 03:32.777
Offer him some escape
from the oppressive monotony

03:32.821 --> 03:35.389
of his, uh,
pathetic own reality.

03:35.432 --> 03:36.781
Give him something

03:36.825 --> 03:40.220
that he, uh, could have
only gotten from you.

03:40.263 --> 03:42.874
Otherwise, what's the point
of being a writer at all?

03:44.180 --> 03:46.487
A good book isn't something
to pass the time...

03:46.530 --> 03:47.531
[sirens wailing]

03:47.575 --> 03:50.491
It should make
your goddamn day.

03:56.540 --> 03:59.282
- Fuck, pick up, pick up,
pick up, pick up.

04:00.414 --> 04:02.894
[phone rings, buzzes]

04:03.634 --> 04:05.027
- Ah.

04:05.593 --> 04:07.682
[ringing, buzzing continue]

04:11.338 --> 04:12.904
Well...

04:12.948 --> 04:15.733
seems we certainly got
his attention.

04:15.777 --> 04:18.475
[chuckles]

04:18.519 --> 04:19.694
[sniffs]

04:19.737 --> 04:22.523
I guess he loves you, huh?

04:22.566 --> 04:24.438
- Answer it.
- [muffled whimper]

04:24.481 --> 04:26.614
[shaky breathing]

04:26.657 --> 04:29.007
- Pick up, God damn it!

04:29.051 --> 04:30.574
Fuck.

04:30.618 --> 04:33.969
- No, we'll let him
spend the night worrying.

04:34.535 --> 04:36.580
The thing about anxiety,

04:36.624 --> 04:38.669
takes on a life of its own.

04:38.713 --> 04:41.106
The mind begins to play tricks,

04:41.150 --> 04:43.935
imagining all the bad things
that can happen.

04:44.719 --> 04:46.503
Well, I don't need to tell you.

04:46.547 --> 04:48.244
- [sniffles]

04:48.288 --> 04:51.726
- Tomorrow, he'll be desperate
to do whatever we tell him,

04:51.769 --> 04:53.771
and he'll be sleep deprived.

04:53.815 --> 04:56.644
- What if he's called
the police already?

04:56.687 --> 04:58.733
- You watch
too much television.

04:59.429 --> 05:02.084
We need to cut down
on his screen time, huh?

05:02.127 --> 05:04.869
- [muffled whimpering]
- Enough, okay?

05:04.913 --> 05:07.219
Nobody likes a whiner.
It's not attractive.

05:09.570 --> 05:11.746
- [grunts]

05:15.053 --> 05:16.968
[glass tinkling]

05:19.057 --> 05:20.885
[phone ringing]

05:23.105 --> 05:24.889
Oh, Jesus, Peter.

05:24.933 --> 05:27.283
Peter, hey.
- He's got Mom.

05:27.327 --> 05:29.198
- I know, I know,
but who is he?

05:29.241 --> 05:30.286
What is going on?

05:31.592 --> 05:33.637
- I found the Rothstein books
in the car.

05:33.942 --> 05:37.206
This guy,
probably Rothstein's killer,

05:37.249 --> 05:38.816
he knows I have the books.

05:38.860 --> 05:40.775
He's looking to make a deal.

05:40.818 --> 05:42.864
He'll release Mom
in exchange for the books.

05:42.907 --> 05:45.040
- Oh, fuck.
Where are you?

05:45.083 --> 05:46.433
- I'm not gonna say where,
I don't want to--

05:46.476 --> 05:48.522
- Ah, Jesus, fuck, Peter!
Come on, man!

05:48.565 --> 05:50.175
- Out of town,
but don't ask me where.

05:50.219 --> 05:51.394
He's probably looking
at the house

05:51.438 --> 05:53.701
hoping you'll lead him to me.

05:53.744 --> 05:57.487
I'd give him the books,
but then he'll kill Mom.

05:57.531 --> 06:00.142
- I know, I know,
they called here too.

06:00.185 --> 06:01.535
- He did?
- Yeah, yeah.

06:01.578 --> 06:03.841
He said if I--
if I reported her missing,

06:03.885 --> 06:05.539
if I so much
as even talk to the police--

06:05.582 --> 06:07.105
- I'm so sorry, Dad.

06:07.149 --> 06:08.672
I--I should have
listened to you.

06:09.717 --> 06:12.328
- Look, buddy,
part of me thinks

06:12.372 --> 06:13.634
we need to call
the police on this.

06:13.677 --> 06:16.898
- No, no, no, no.
- Fuck, Pete, we need help!

06:16.941 --> 06:19.379
- This guy we're dealing with,
he killed Rothstein,

06:19.422 --> 06:21.511
the bookstore owner.

06:21.555 --> 06:25.080
As long as I have the books,
he'll need to keep Mom alive.

06:25.123 --> 06:27.082
- We have to come up
with some kind of a plan here,

06:27.125 --> 06:28.388
otherwise, she is fucked.

06:28.431 --> 06:29.432
She is gonna--
they're gonna kill her.

06:29.476 --> 06:30.999
[doorbell rings]

06:31.042 --> 06:33.218
[Boogers barking]

06:33.262 --> 06:35.438
Somebody's here.
- What? Who?

06:35.482 --> 06:37.222
[knocking at door]

06:37.266 --> 06:39.050
- Stay by your phone.
- No, no, no, no!

06:39.094 --> 06:40.922
Don't answer the door.
It's probably him.

06:40.965 --> 06:42.227
Don't--
- I don't know, I don't know.

06:42.271 --> 06:44.316
Just stay by your phone.
I'll call you back.

06:44.360 --> 06:46.623
[Boogers barking]
[knocking continues]

06:52.150 --> 06:53.978
Boogers, get away.

06:54.501 --> 06:56.503
Okay.

07:07.122 --> 07:08.950
- Uh, listen, I know it'searly, but something's come up.

07:08.993 --> 07:10.125
Can I come in for a second?

07:10.168 --> 07:12.606
- It's, um--it's not
a good time, Bill.

07:12.649 --> 07:13.998
- It's kind of important.

07:14.869 --> 07:16.610
- Can it wait?
- "Can it wait"?

07:16.653 --> 07:18.133
Your son is missing.

07:20.178 --> 07:21.832
Is he still missing?

07:22.398 --> 07:24.008
- Yes, he's missing.

07:25.793 --> 07:28.099
- Are you all right?
- No, Bill, I'm not all right.

07:28.143 --> 07:30.014
My son is missing.
I'm a fucking wreck.

07:30.058 --> 07:33.104
- But whatever I might have,
it can wait.

07:36.107 --> 07:37.500
- What do you have?

07:39.154 --> 07:40.547
- Okay.

07:41.373 --> 07:43.941
This is Peter in the bookstore

07:43.985 --> 07:46.509
where the owner
was just found killed.

07:48.555 --> 07:49.904
- What are you saying?

07:49.947 --> 07:51.514
You--you think
he's a suspect in that?

07:51.558 --> 07:53.560
- I think
exactly what you think:

07:53.951 --> 07:55.126
that he went in there

07:55.170 --> 07:57.259
to sell the stolen
Rothstein manuscripts.

07:57.738 --> 08:00.262
Did he ever mention
Andrew Halliday to you?

08:00.654 --> 08:01.959
- No.

08:02.960 --> 08:04.179
- Can I get a cup of tea--

08:04.222 --> 08:06.007
- It's not a--
not a good time, Bill.

08:06.050 --> 08:08.531
[stammers]
I'm not feeling well and...

08:11.534 --> 08:13.144
- Is somebody here?

08:13.710 --> 08:16.496
- No, o-other than Marjorie,
who's in bed.

08:16.539 --> 08:18.454
She--she took a pill.

08:18.498 --> 08:20.891
Why don't I come down
to your office, um,

08:20.935 --> 08:22.371
later this morning, huh?

08:23.590 --> 08:25.417
- You don't seem yourself.

08:26.070 --> 08:28.203
- My son is missing, Bill.

08:29.073 --> 08:30.727
- What's going on, Tom?

08:32.076 --> 08:33.904
- It's not a good time.

08:47.048 --> 08:48.310
[phone clicks]

08:48.353 --> 08:52.575
[keys tap]

08:52.619 --> 08:54.490
[phone line trilling]

09:01.192 --> 09:02.150
[phone line beeps]

09:02.193 --> 09:03.543
- Hey, Holly.

09:04.369 --> 09:06.502
Something weird's going on
with Tom Saubers' house.

09:06.546 --> 09:07.895
- Should we call the police?

09:07.938 --> 09:10.375
- Uh, there's nothing
really to report.

09:10.419 --> 09:12.726
- But you suspect
something's up, right?

09:12.769 --> 09:15.772
- I know something's up.
You at the office?

09:15.816 --> 09:18.122
- Uh, no, I'm at home with Lou.

09:18.166 --> 09:19.646
- How's she doing?

09:20.211 --> 09:22.126
- Um, she's settling in.

09:22.170 --> 09:23.432
- All right, call Jerome.

09:23.475 --> 09:24.868
Tell him get the hell
into the office.

09:24.912 --> 09:25.869
- Got it.

09:25.913 --> 09:28.045
- I do not have a good feeling.

09:29.438 --> 09:31.179
- That was Bill.

09:32.267 --> 09:34.312
- Yeah?
Was he talking about me?

09:34.356 --> 09:36.619
- [laughs]
- My sphincter was itching.

09:36.663 --> 09:38.099
[laughs]

09:38.142 --> 09:40.057
- We're gonna be worried
about you, Lou, you know?

09:40.101 --> 09:41.624
I suggest you get used to it.

09:44.322 --> 09:45.846
- So I--I was thinking

09:45.889 --> 09:47.369
that maybe I could help out
at the office a little bit.

09:47.412 --> 09:48.762
You don't have to pay me
or anything--

09:48.805 --> 09:50.720
- Yeah.
- But I could, uh, you know--

09:50.764 --> 09:53.070
it might help to occupy
myself while I, um,

09:53.462 --> 09:55.420
- look for work.
- Totally, yeah.

09:55.464 --> 09:58.423
- I could help with the
computers, spell Jerome some.

09:58.467 --> 09:59.642
[phone rings]

09:59.686 --> 10:01.339
- That'd be gre--
sorry, one second.

10:01.383 --> 10:03.254
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, no.
Totally, totally.

10:03.298 --> 10:04.734
- Hello?

10:05.082 --> 10:07.171
This--this is Holly.

10:07.563 --> 10:09.173
Holly Gibney.

10:11.219 --> 10:13.264
Uh, excuse me?

10:15.832 --> 10:18.661
[stammers] Sorry, is this
some kind of joke?

10:20.445 --> 10:23.144
O-okay, I'll have
to call you back later.

10:23.448 --> 10:24.711
Thank you.

10:25.886 --> 10:28.279
- Who was that?
Was that Finkelstein?

10:29.498 --> 10:32.414
- No, it was not Finkelstein.

10:35.025 --> 10:38.202
- [moaning]
Yeah!

10:38.246 --> 10:42.076
Morris, come on, come on!
[stammers]

10:42.119 --> 10:44.295
- Oh, yes.
- Morris, what are you--

10:44.339 --> 10:45.732
[stammers]
Ooh!

10:45.775 --> 10:47.690
What the hell
has gotten into you?

10:47.734 --> 10:50.475
- [grunts]
Ow!

10:50.519 --> 10:52.739
The hell is that?
- You tell me!

10:52.782 --> 10:54.566
- [grunts]
What are you talking about?

10:54.610 --> 10:55.742
What's wrong with you?

10:55.785 --> 10:57.961
- You were making love to her,
not me.

10:58.005 --> 11:00.398
You've been making love to her
ever since I told you.

11:00.442 --> 11:02.444
- Told me what?
- Don't bullshit me, Morris.

11:02.487 --> 11:03.837
You're fucking Susan.

11:03.880 --> 11:05.708
The Susan in the book.

11:05.752 --> 11:07.667
- I'm fucking both of you.

11:07.710 --> 11:10.017
You said she's you, so what
difference does it make?

11:10.060 --> 11:11.496
- It makes a big difference!

11:11.540 --> 11:13.498
- She was based on you!

11:13.542 --> 11:15.022
It was your idea
that I fuck you this way

11:15.065 --> 11:16.110
in the first place!

11:16.153 --> 11:18.112
- Once!
Not always.

11:18.155 --> 11:20.723
You're either all in with me
or you're not in at all.

11:20.767 --> 11:22.377
- [scoffs]
You know what?

11:22.420 --> 11:24.640
I can't keep track
of all your insanity.

11:24.684 --> 11:26.250
Somebody needs
to invent an app.

11:26.294 --> 11:29.427
- Oh, for God's sake,
did you take a pill?

11:29.471 --> 11:30.820
- What?
-We're having a fight,

11:30.864 --> 11:31.778
for fuck's sake!

11:31.821 --> 11:33.301
You're not even discouraged!

11:33.344 --> 11:34.955
- I did not take a pill.

11:34.998 --> 11:36.565
- Because you don't need to,
do you?

11:36.608 --> 11:38.698
No, you have her.
You have your little Susan.

11:38.741 --> 11:40.351
- Who is you!

11:40.395 --> 11:43.528
[grunts]
- [grunts]

11:43.572 --> 11:46.314
I'm Susan to Rothstein,
not to you.

11:46.357 --> 11:47.445
[wails]

11:47.489 --> 11:49.404
- Why does it
make a difference?

11:49.447 --> 11:53.103
- [whining]
Because it does!

11:53.147 --> 11:54.539
[sobbing]

11:54.583 --> 11:56.280
- [sighs]
[door slams]

11:56.324 --> 11:58.065
[engine rumbling]

11:59.588 --> 12:02.547
- Uh, the case is closed,
and according to probate,

12:02.591 --> 12:04.506
you're the bequeathed.

12:04.549 --> 12:06.116
- I'm not sure I want it.

12:06.160 --> 12:07.727
- Oh, you can probably
sell it on eBay

12:07.770 --> 12:09.467
for some obscene
amount of money.

12:09.511 --> 12:11.426
- Operative word
being "obscene."

12:11.469 --> 12:13.384
- No, it still ranks
as a collector.

12:13.428 --> 12:15.909
You know, the low miles,
in pretty good shape.

12:16.344 --> 12:17.998
[brakes squeaking]

12:18.041 --> 12:20.827
Or we can, you know, haul it
off and have it crushed--

12:20.870 --> 12:22.698
at your expense, of course--
but it--like I said,

12:22.742 --> 12:25.135
it--it's worth something
to a collector.

12:25.179 --> 12:28.356
Replace the windshield
and it's drivable.

12:28.399 --> 12:31.620
[sinister music]

12:31.663 --> 12:36.581
♪

12:36.625 --> 12:39.454
Are you okay?

12:39.497 --> 12:40.585
[music fades]

12:40.629 --> 12:43.066
- Yeah, I'm fine.

12:47.114 --> 12:49.725
- Where's Holly?
- She said she had to go out.

12:49.769 --> 12:51.814
- She, uh, gave me
some chores to do.

12:51.858 --> 12:55.296
Thought I'd earn my keepa little while I look for work.

12:55.339 --> 12:57.080
I made you some coffee.

13:00.170 --> 13:02.520
- Thanks, good.

13:02.564 --> 13:04.740
- Hey, I've got
something for you.

13:05.219 --> 13:07.743
Gotta show you something.
It's important.

13:10.311 --> 13:11.834
Remember him?

13:13.314 --> 13:15.098
- Stan the man.

13:15.142 --> 13:16.273
- Yeah.

13:17.057 --> 13:19.711
Cops found DNA in the shop
and the getaway car

13:19.755 --> 13:20.930
and none of it
belonged to Stan.

13:20.974 --> 13:23.150
But check this out.

13:23.541 --> 13:26.022
ER reports from the guy
who showed up to the hospital

13:26.066 --> 13:28.198
when the getaway car crashed
into that basin.

13:30.200 --> 13:31.898
First and second page.

13:34.509 --> 13:36.946
- Nah, I can't read this shit.

13:36.990 --> 13:40.558
- Okay, it just says
that the guy at the ER's DNA

13:40.602 --> 13:43.300
matches the DNA found in
the shop and the getaway car.

13:43.344 --> 13:44.780
So...

13:45.520 --> 13:48.653
I mean, the guy who did
the Rothstein job killed Stan.

13:48.697 --> 13:50.046
- Which we already figured.

13:50.090 --> 13:51.482
- Yes, yes, I'm not done.

13:52.179 --> 13:54.224
The cops found DNA in
the Saubers' home last week--

13:54.268 --> 13:57.445
I mean, saliva,
prints, everything--

13:57.488 --> 13:59.447
and it matches
with the same guy.

13:59.490 --> 14:01.057
- What?
- Yeah.

14:01.101 --> 14:02.842
The killer
was in the Saubers' house,

14:03.146 --> 14:06.454
so, I mean,
maybe Pete was involved.

14:07.411 --> 14:08.978
